article.headline: Northeastern 88, Cornell 85
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. (AP) -- Juan Barea scored 35 points and made the winning basket with 0.9 seconds remaining Saturday night in Northeastern's 88-85 victory over Cornell in the third-place game of the Marist Classic. Barea scored Northeastern's last 14 points and shot 6-of-12 from 3-point range. He added five assists, five rebounds and two steals. Backcourt mate Marcus Barnes added 23 points and four assists for the Huskies (1-1). Cody Toppert had 20 points and five assists for Cornell (0-2). Eric Taylor had 14 points and 16 rebounds for his sixth career double-double, and Lenny Collins and Graham Dow also scored 14 points each. The Big Red connected on 55 percent of their field goals, but committed 13 turnovers compared to six for Northeastern. Cornell led by seven with 3:02 to play before Barea made three straight 3-pointers over a span of 1:14. He then hit a pair of free throws to tie it 85-85 with 49 seconds left and followed that with a step-back 3 that won it.
